canonical:
  title: 王太子加元服敎書
  author: 崔洪胤
  language: lzh
  text: 敎王太子 諱立儲必先賢主器莫若長眷予副貳爲國本根日就月將早勵元良之德川冲玉裕合膺監務之權矧當志學之年盍賜成人之服玆加縟禮用示殊恩庶勤夙夜之心紹復祖宗之業今遣攝太尉兼賓佐理同德功臣特進開府儀同三司金紫光祿大夫守太師門下侍郞同中書門下平章事修文殿大學士監脩國史判尙書禮部事太子大傅任濡攝司徒兼冠具官李抗等賫持敎書往彼宣諭故玆敎示
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 王太子加元服敎書
  author: 崔洪胤
  language: lzh
  text: 敎王太子 諱。立儲必先賢。主器莫若長。眷予副貳。爲國本根。日就月將。早勵元良之德。川冲玉裕。合膺監務之權。矧當志學之年。盍賜成人之服。玆加縟禮。用示殊恩。庶勤夙夜之心。紹復祖宗之業。今遣攝太尉兼賓佐理同德功臣特進開府儀同三司金紫光祿大夫守太師門下侍郞同中書門下平章事修文殿大學士監脩國史判尙書禮部事太子大傅任濡。攝司徒兼冠具官李抗等。賫持敎書。往彼宣諭。故玆敎示。
korean:
  title: 왕태자 가 원복 교서
  author: 최홍윤
  language: kor
  text: 왕태자 휘(諱) 에게 교하노라. 저군(儲君)을 세우는 데는 반드시 어진 이를 먼저하고, 후사를 맡는 데는 큰아들이 제일이다. 사랑하는 나의 태자는 나라의 근본이 된다. 학문이 날로 늘어나고 달로 진보되어 일찍이 원량(元良)의 덕을 닦았고, 덕이 물같이 깊고 옥같이 온화하니 감무(監務)의 직책을 맡기에 적합하다. 하물며 학문에 뜻을 두는 나이가 되었으니 어찌 성인(成人)이 되는 옷을 입지 않으리오. 이에 화려한 예식으로 특수한 은혜를 보이는 것이다. 바라건대 일찍 일어나고 밤 늦게 자는 마음을 부지런히 하여 조종의 업을 이을지어다.이제 섭태위겸빈 좌리동덕공신 특진개부의 동삼사 금자광록대부 수 태사 문하시랑 동 중서문하평장사 수문전태학사 감수국사 판상서 예부사 태자태부(攝太尉兼賓佐理同德功臣特進開府儀同三司金紫光祿大夫守太師門下侍郞同中書門下平章事修文殿太學士監修國史判尙書禮部事太子太傅) 임유(任濡)와 섭사도 겸관구관(攝司徒兼冠具官) 이항(李抗) 등을 보내어 교서를 가지고 그 곳에 가서 선유(宣諭)하게 하였다. 그러므로 이에 교시한다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0260_020_0250&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Edict Upon the Conferment of Adult Robes to the Crown Prince
  author: Choe Hong-yun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    To the Crown Prince, whose name is withheld:

    When establishing an heir to the throne, one must first choose the virtuous; when entrusting the succession, the eldest son is paramount. You, my beloved heir apparent, are the foundation of our realm. Your learning grows with each passing day and each turning month—early have you cultivated the virtue of the worthy heir. Your character flows like water and shines like jade, befitting one to bear the trust of governance. And now that you have reached the age of scholarly ambition, how can you not don the robes of manhood? Therefore do we conduct this grand ceremony, that all may know the special favor we bestow upon you. May you preserve diligence in rising early and retiring late, that you may continue the great work of your ancestors and preserve their legacy.

    We hereby dispatch the Acting Grand General and Ceremonial Officer, Merit Keeper of Shared Virtue, Special Emissary and Minister of the Inner Circle, Bearer of Purple Insignia and Guardian of the Royal Treasury, Keeper of the Eastern Palace and Attendant of the Imperial Gate, Co-Administrator of the Imperial Secretariat and Editor of the National History, Minister supervising the Bureau of Rites and Grand Tutor to the Crown Prince, Rim Yu, together with the Acting Minister of Works and Keeper of the Coronation Regalia, Yi Kang, and others, who shall carry this edict and proceed to make proclamation. Thus we make this instruction known.
  footnotes:
    - This edict marks the coming-of-age ceremony (gwanrye, 관례) for the crown prince, a crucial ritual in East Asian monarchies signifying the transition to manhood and official recognition of his role as heir.
    - The phrase '元良' (won-ryang) refers to a worthy and virtuous heir apparent, a classical ideal in Confucian governance.
    - The extensive list of titles reflects the high official rank and ceremonial importance of those selected to present the edict, underscoring the solemnity of the occasion.
